5. Explain Switch Port 

ANS-A switch port is a physical interface on a network switch that connects devices like computers or other switches.
 It operates at Layer 2, forwarding frames based on MAC addresses. 
Ports can be configured as access (single VLAN) or trunk (multiple VLANs) modes,
 Supporting network segmentation and communication.


6- An engineer connects to Router R1 and issues a show ip ospf neighbor command. 
The status of neighbor 2.2.2.2 lists FULL/BDR. What does the BDR mean? 
A. R1 is an Area Border Router. 
B. R1 is a backup designated router. 
C. Router 2.2.2.2 is an Area Border Router. 
D. Router 2.2.2.2 is a backup designated router. 

ANS-D. Router 2.2.2.2 is a backup designated router.



7- Which command is used to view the neighbor discovery table on a PC? 
A. show ipv6 neighbor 
B. show ipv6 neighbors 
C. netsh interface ipv6 show neighbor 
D. netsh interface ipv6 show neighbors 

ANS-C. netsh interface ipv6 show neighbor


